,Not Recommended,537860,26009987,"Posted: 13 October, 2016",all,Azra'eil,"I bought this game on sale for  e0.60. Figured it would be worth that much because I like simple tower defense games.The reviews, apparently, were very positive, but when I searched for them manually later, most of them were negative.But this piece of crap doesn't even work half of the time. The game runs, don't get me wrong, but the towers don't shoot properly while in range of the enemies. And when they do, they do so unreliably. The faster you set your game speed, the more accurate they become, but getting the core basics of a game wrong (i.e. shooting stuff) is a no-no for me.  Your little nephew (age 8) could probably make a better game.2/10TL:DR got fooled by Steam review manipulation; this is a sh!t game."
,Not Recommended,537860,26591918,"Posted: 13 November, 2016",all,kumori,"After 100% achievments: This game is as bad as it is ugly. Bugs, broken mechanics and poor balance. I spent so much time with it because the ""New Game"" is just next to ""Continue"" and will wipe your game progress without asking first.It starts up as nwjs.exe (meaning northwind.js). So quite literally a javascript browser game running in a browser environment. (NwJS runs javascript using chromes javascript engine.) Another more obvious hint is that if you load your game instead of starting a new one, the score will constantly say NaN (which means ""Not a Number"" in javascript world). That is a programmer goof if I ever saw one. And yet the dev pushes it live and sells the game for money? Classy. I'm sure there can be good games made with purely javascript, but this is not it.The napalm tower has a bullet that explodes on impact and does AoE damage. The  thing is that when it detonates it also triggers all other bullets of the same type to detonate. Meaning if you have one of those towers close to the path, and another far from the path. The tower far from the path will never hit anything as long as the first tower is firing. And the game is riddled with this kind of broken silliness. You are fighting the game breaking bugs and not the monsters.Still, the napalm tower is the only viable tower... wait for it...In all the 10 levels! Great balancing there!I could rage on this for days, but I'll keep it short to save my soul: Don't get this game. Not for cheap, not for free."
,Not Recommended,537860,26409621,"Posted: 3 November, 2016",all,Apoc,"The first 5 levels are fun... Then you end up on Level 6 and you find out the only way to win against the new enemy type is placing napalm towers at the exact right spots. You repeat this for the last 4 levels and you are done.Difficulty level does not seems to matter much and beating the game on a harder difficulty does not seems to change anything.There is also a score but it is glitched and always say NaN.There are really costly towers but you can't really afford them while upgrading your Napalm army and the weaker towers don't really do anything past the first levels.Some towers actually shot projectiles and those can miss depending on placement and enemy speed, it's interesting but also infuriating since you can't really guess before placing them.I could not really understand the target priority, sometimes a tower will let an almost dead enemy pass and attack some other farther back without a second though.You also can't switch target priority, the only options are upgrading or selling a tower and upgrading simply boost the stats, no special bonus for tower types.In game there is a sound button but it does not do anything, you have to exit to the main menu to go in the options.It is a really short game in need of a lot of balancing, 75% of my playtime was spent on level 6.In its current state I can't recommend it, at least it is cheap."
